caption: I like this place! They prepare first-rate food, they have a nice menu, The cook in that restaurant is a real authority in the kitchen, I love very much tasting all their dishes. The dishes are always good, the attitude towards the guests  is very good too. I often eat in this place and I was never unsatisfied. Highly recommended.
I really enjoyed their food. I always get good customer service there. The place is always clean and the staff members are always super nice. Will come visit again.
I eat in this spot a lot since I work close by. I like how their service is always awesome and they keep the spot well kept at all times. Pricing is affordable and they serve big portions.

I often take my friends to this place with my warmest recommendations. I visit this restaurant often. This recommendation is always successful. The dishes they serve are delicious and the crew is welcoming and cooperative. Every time  we visit this place we have a pleasant evening.  I recommend this place with pleasure.
Fantastic and yummy food, I love the mood the place has, and the workers were kind. Will surely visit here again.
This spot is awesome and roomy, the menu was delicious and the rates were very inexpensive. quick, productive service and very personal staff members. I recommend this place.
Had a very good experience in this spot with my friend. The food comes out quickly and the service is just great. Prices are convenient.
My fave!! Affordable and quality food.
We ordered two seafood tofu soap for take out, just give me this 3 little sides? Oh my god! I can’t believe it, so bad!...
Exceptional and yummy food, I love the character the spot has, and the cashiers were welcoming. I will surely visit here again.
Very good and clean!

Got take out.  Ordered on site and the food was prepared quickly.  Bibimbap was great!  They put the rice in separate containers which made it keep better till we got home.  Included Kim chi, fish cakes, and cucumber as side dishes. Fried dumplings 🥟 were tasty.  Wish that this location had spicy rice cakes.
It’s very delicious Korean food. The place is nice and clean 👍🏻
An excellent stop in Quincy for Korean food
Good food, good service, what's not to like!
I love it here! The foods really delicious and the actual place inside is really nice looking.  And I like the music that they play.
The customer service is constantly rapid, excellent atmosphere, very nice staff. Will visit again when I arrive in town.

(Translated by Google) (2nd review: We paid and only got a receipt for the restaurant, but the receipt on the restaurant disappeared for unknown reasons, the staff kept waiting for us to assume that we took it, and we didn't pick up the receipt for the restaurant, They don't even have a solution and embarrass us without suggesting a solution, and when we ask what to do then we say we need to sign a new receipt, so we need a lot of sense to suggest a solution before we embarrass.) It's very nice place to eat korean foods because the staff was so kind, serving was and foods (Tofu bibimbap, tofu stew) were so delicious. I definitly recommend this restaurant for you. Dishes tastes good,services was very fast and good.nice place
Very delicious. The bibimbap is the the best.
Menu is small, but everything is yummy. I love the radish side dish.
Great food and service
The food is regularly fresh and tasty, staff members gives good service. I loved how neat it is and atmosphere. Keep up the good work.
I visit this spot a lot since I work in the area. I must say their customer service is always awesome and they keep the place well kept regularly. Pricing is fair and they serve sizeable portions.
We were greeted warmly, and it just got better from there.  Food service and pricing perfect

I lived in South Korea for 4 year and very familiar with the food. Since moving to Boston been looking for a reasonably priced and high quality Korean soup resturant. SGD Dubu has the best soups I’ve had since living here. They also provided 5 small side dishes and refilled my kimchi. $14 for lunch was bomb
loved this truly authentic korean restaurant
Beef is amazing
Tofu soup is great, seafood pancake is so so - texture isn’t that good.

Didnt have to wait long. Very clean place. Good looking staff. Nice people. Fast and accommodating. Restaurant smelled like good food. The dishes were good. Plain soup was a tad bit salty for me but still enjoyed it. Loved that they still gave me egg in my soup. Egg was cooked nicely. Bit runny on inside was good. Like eggs more raw but that is just me. Want to visit again to try the short ribs. Looked so good sizzling on the plate.

I went around 2pm on a Tuesday. As always, I try to avoid rush hours. When I arrived, only two tables were occupied so service prompt. Immediately offered water and a menu, and as soon as I made eye contact the servers would stop for me. I ordered the hot stone beef bibimbap (dolsot bibimbap bulgolgi). While I agree that the amount of beef is small for American standards, it seems well portioned in other aspects. I like to mix my bibimbap though so it is enough to spread through the dish. It comes with side dishes (banchan) which is nice, but I have to commend the egg soup that the dish came with. Although considered a side, it was refreshing in a salty brothy way. Just as a side note, I prefer my bibimbap to have a fried egg on top, but they make the bibimbap with the egg already in the dish. I'm sure they can do that for you if you ask however.
Love the food here
Good, but side dishes are so so.
Great service and amazing food. No frills, no fake smiling BS, just real responsive good people who will put a delicious meal in front of you.

Great dumplings. Great seafood pancake.  The hot stone bibimbap came on a stone plate instead of the pot... the amount of beef in the bibimbap plate left a bit to be desired. The soup dish also was lacking meat.  The presentation was nice though and food was tasty.  The menu is very simple...
Small menu but usually well prepared and tasty.
My girlfriend and I loved going to the SGD in New Jersey when she used to live there. Now that she's moved to Boston, we can get our fix here. Same menu, great food.
Clean and spacious place. Delicious food.

LOUD music for a restaurant as if it is a club or  a bar. You go to a restaurant, kick back and relax and have nice dinner but this place is nothing but. Very unpleasant. Good food though. Will not be back.
My favorite Koerean place in the area. One customer told me he travels all the way from the city just to eat here. Having spent 3 years in Korea I appreciate their authentic food and environment.
Love the Korean bbq

Loved this place! I thought the beef Bulgogi was delicious, the kimchi was good but I think it needed to marinate another day because the flavor was a bit light but it was still good! Love when places serve the radishes! The service was wonderful as well and I will certainly be back!
A very nice place with good food
Very very limited on the menu but really good if you know what to order
Delicious
Tasty and delicious
Love the short ribs. Not a big menu but everything I've had, I've enjoyed.  I go here with friends at least once a month, if not more.
Great beef short rib. Tofu stew with dumpling is good. Order it with high spice level if you want spicy.

(Translated by Google) This is a very delicious Korean cuisine唷🇰🇷 The restaurant is clean and good. After going to the Golden Gate supermarket to buy food, you have to come here to eat! ! !  (Original) 這家是很好吃的韓國料理唷🇰🇷 餐廳乾淨服務很好，以後去金門超市買菜都要來這吃飯！！！
Well prepared dubu (tofu) with good choices of accompanying items (meat/vegetables and rice/various noodles) as well as spice level. Dol sot bibimbap was delicious.

Went here with a friend on Monday night as it can get real busy on the weekends. The boiled dumplings are very good. So is there "SOONDUBU STEW " korean hot soup regular Bowl of kimchi, beef, pork, seafood, vegetable tofu or chicken. Then Pick between 5 spice levels. BE CAREFUL even the plain has some hot spice. Then pick if you want kalguksu (flat noodles), ramen or hot stone bowl rice. Service was excellent! Refills of the side dishes that came with the soup were very generous. Always asking if we wanted more. Our server was also great at making sure our water and tea glasses were always full as well as explaining the menu to people totally not familiar with the food. The prices are very reasonable. Next i want to try the "BIBIMBAP" STEAMED RICE WITH ASSORTED, SAUTEED, AND SEASONED VEGETABLES SERVED ON A TRADITIONAL KOREAN HOT STONE PLATE. *No gimbap available. :-(
Decent dishes, affordable lunch and dinner menus.
cheap Soondofu were expensive here.
So good, soup especially during winter.
Finally Delicious Korean food in Quincy!

It's a good place for a Korean bbq. Its just that their dishes could do a little bit better with taste. Not saying it's bad. It's a good place! But just not the best.. maybe I'm being harsh. But we were a group of 8 adults and 3 children. They were not busy and had helpers. They should have been at their best..

Not many dishes; those that they have are average to below average  - nothing to yearn for.  Beef bulgogi is a bit too sweet, and ramen tasted like instant noodle.  As for the atmosphere, it’s as basic as it can be: I might even say it’s a step up from a take out.  Price wise, it’s average to a bit high given the average quality of the foods and comparing to other restaurants.  I’d recommend an improvement to the menu and food quality.
Ordered their beef short ribs and kimchi stew with hot stone bowl rice. Very tasty Korean food! Glad to have an awesome Korean restaurant nearby! The staff were also nice to us!
Meals not bad but you can't sell liquors
Very tasty. Love scraping that crispy burned rice off the bottom of the stone bowl.
My second time loved great food fair price staff was  awesome
Amazing tofu soup, short ribs, seafood pancake, and bulgogi
very nice
Food here is delicious. Great service. Definitely worth the price.
The atmosphere nice and the food is pretty good! The whole feel to this place and food is very homey great place highly recommended!

We have been here several times at this point.  The food is consistent and good. The staff on the other hand is young, clearly very inexperienced and untrained in the art of service. You always feel the pressure of a frantic server running about as they either have way to many servers and you just watch them stand around or not enough and they give you anxiety from the staffs stress level.  Owners, train your staff.. Very unwelcoming, cold and frantic atmosphere.
Great service and great food.

This was a great find!   Very tasty soft tofu soups with great value.  They even give you white rice in hot stone bowls!!!   That was simply awesome!!!   I ate the scorched rice at the bottom of the stone bowl and it took me back to my childhood!  ;-)   Also, we were quite impressed that the servers came by to give refills of the side dishes that were either low or empty... without having to ask for them!!!  That is service!!!   ;-)   Go try this place... a bit busy in the parking lot (Kam Man is just a hot mess there everyday) but well worth the visit!!!
The Kimchi stew is delicious and filling. Really enjoyed the rice getting crispy in the hot stone bowl. Generous offerings of different Korean pickles to start off. Very delicious
I’ve been five times now! Service is awesome. Mom and I really loved their beef short ribs. Free appetizers are abundant too.

This place is great local Korean restaurant.  If you want to go to a place with a simple menu then this is the place.  The tofu dish is awesome as the spicy level can be changed and you can noodles or rice in the stone pot.  The rice in the stone pot when left, will create a crunch that goes great with the tofu.  Here's a tip, if there's still rice in the stone bowl but it's stuck against the bowl, ask for some tea from the wait staff to pour into the bowl.  This will give you another meal with your tofu dish!  🍚🍚
My favorite restaurant ever! The people that work there are so nice. I live a hour away but it's worth it!
Great customer services.
Probably the best place to get decent Korean food in Quincy
Attentive service, very good food, will go back.
Great authentic Korean food helps me satisfied my craving. Friendly staffs, fast service even when the restaurant is full of crowded. Definitely coming back to try other items on the Menu.
Food is good and service is efficient.  Price is a little high but it’s a good try
Simple and basic menu, good tofu soup and rice dishes. The Korean pancake is nice too. Nothing fancy but tastes good. Service is above average. The restaurant is clean and a bit on the spacious side.
Great to have a good Korean restaurant nearby in Quincy.  Was very satisfied with the taste.
